metadata.name: Deep Seed #30
metadata.description:
"An ancient sketchbook of unknown origin with text that I cant translate.
Filled with many pencil-drawn sketches.
Which in my opinion could be drawings of ancient life forms, probably marine.

Who knows maybe we are looking at the deep seed of art!?"

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 's' to save .png with resolution = 6000px x 6000px
- press 'n' to save .png with resolution = 9000px x 9000px

metadata.name: The Three-Body Problem #72
metadata.description:
The Three-Body Problem refers to the difficulty in evaluating an analytical expression for an object under the influence of two massive bodies. This work shows the gravitational vector field from two such bodies. Occasionally, lines will also show curves of equipotential in this field, the centre of mass of the system, the orbital paths traced out. The system is periodic and will loop forever.

Press UP to export one second of frames, and DOWN to save an SVG from the current frame.

metadata.name: Cogito, Ergo Sum #46
metadata.description:
The artwork 'Cogito, Ergo Sum' ('I think, therefore I am,' René Descartes) is an artist's exploration of the human nature of thinking. How similar is the way of thinking for all people? How different are the emotional patterns that affect our thought processes, and how are they interrelated? Do this particular moment in time (the time of the work creation) and the particular person (collector) affect the final result (for the visual solution of a piece)?

Some philosophy, some metaphysics, the participation of real people, and the result of the research are 155 works from the 'Cogito, Ergo Sum' collection.

*The collection is based on the @m5alien artist's idea that new art is born in collaboration between artist, algorithm, and collector.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #471
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.name: filaments #30
metadata.description:
A simulation using differential growth, imitating simple life-forms resembling bacteria.
The points in each filament attract and repel each other, to form doodle-like shapes in the end.
